    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5935" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μακρός</span></b> , comp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μακρότερος</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μᾶσσον</span>, sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μακρότατος</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">long, tall</span>, of space and of time (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέλευθος, ἤματα</span>), and of things that are high
          or deep (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὔρεα, δένδρα, φρείατα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.197</span></i>); freq. adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μακρόν, μακρά</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">far, afar</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βοᾶν, ἀῡτεῖν; μακρὰ βιβά̄ς</span>, ‘with
          long strides.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
